            . I am a constable. I saw the prisoner walking with this case of soap on his right shoulder, three or four hundred yards from the prosecutrix's; I asked where he got it - he hesitated, and then said, "I have taken the soap;" I said he must take it back again, and he went back to the shop with it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I picked up this box of soap.</p>
